Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.69,0:00:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We extend a warm welcome to all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.57,0:00:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the December 2019 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.61,0:00:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting®.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.09,0:00:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watchtower Bible School of Gilead
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.72,0:00:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,began on February 1, 1943.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.43,0:00:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of students have benefited
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.77,0:00:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from the school’s in-depth course
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.15,0:00:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After months of intense study,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.73,0:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,graduation day is a highlight for the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.61,0:00:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.74,0:00:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll enjoy Part 1 of the graduation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.04,0:00:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 147th class of Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.62,0:01:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay close attention
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.62,0:01:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to these encouraging Scriptural talks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.08,0:01:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,delivered to the graduates
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.09,0:01:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on Saturday, September 14, 2019.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.22,0:01:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is a very happy day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.22,0:01:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for those\Nwho are very soon to graduate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.55,0:01:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,from this 147th class of Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.89,0:01:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to begin by asking them a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.52,0:01:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is, How far will you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.03,0:01:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now,\Nwhen people ask that question,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.03,0:01:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How far will you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.03,0:01:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,(normally in connection\Nwith secular education)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.24,0:01:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning of the question is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.29,0:01:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to get your bachelor’s degree
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.37,0:01:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or are you going to go for your master’s
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.58,0:01:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or are you going to go for a PhD\Nand get your doctorate?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.42,0:01:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, in that sense,\Noften going far in secular education
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.42,0:01:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is solely a means of self-fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:02:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and not necessarily to help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Some study what’s called pure science,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.64,0:02:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,meant just to advance\Nmankind’s understanding of science
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.48,0:02:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but with no practical benefit;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,some study dead languages;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.49,0:02:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,some study bacteria or insects,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.78,0:02:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which is wonderful if you like insects.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.25,0:02:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It may increase knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn’t necessarily help anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, divine education is so different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it motivates us to ask the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.55,0:02:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How far can I go,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘not to further myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.60,0:02:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but to help others?’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.47,0:02:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jehovah God and Christ Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.06,0:02:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,really set the example for us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.15,0:02:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.44,0:02:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read together Psalm 113,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.40,0:02:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s look here at verse 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:02:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of our wonderful God, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.45,0:03:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it says:\N“He stoops down
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.46,0:03:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to look on heaven and earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.71,0:03:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, how high\Ndo you imagine Jehovah to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.71,0:03:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no matter how high you imagine it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.97,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you know it’s still higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is so high as the Almighty God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.89,0:03:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does it say here in verse 6?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“He stoops down.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, just think.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.90,0:03:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You might think of an illustration\Nof a man who is perhaps very, very tall,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.49,0:03:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s talking to a very, very small child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.36,0:03:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.82,0:03:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, oftentimes he might crouch down,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,get down on one knee,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.33,0:03:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and get right down onto the level\Nof the child to speak to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result,\Nhow does the little child feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not so afraid,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:03:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not so intimidated by that large man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.01,0:03:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The child becomes calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.68,0:04:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, think about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How far has Jehovah gone\Nto “stoop down”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.23,0:04:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we feel loved?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.69,0:04:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we feel valued?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we feel appreciated?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.86,0:04:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful example Jehovah sets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in going far to make us feel
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.82,0:04:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so comfortable with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what about our Lord Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.41,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, think how far he went\Nto help each one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.79,0:04:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at the scripture here\Nin Philippians chapter 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians chapter 2
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.63,0:04:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,says that Jesus, of course,\Ncame from heaven, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.85,0:04:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how far that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It says in verse 5:\N“Keep this mental attitude in you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.02,0:04:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“that was also in Christ Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.23,0:04:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“who, although he was existing in God’s form,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“gave no consideration to a seizure,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.27,0:04:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“namely, that he should be equal to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:04:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but he emptied himself.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.70,0:05:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.74,0:05:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He “took a slave’s form and became human.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.45,0:05:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was pretty far to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.87,0:05:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you and I think the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty amazing and pretty wonderful,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.96,0:05:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have you ever seen heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.96,0:05:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s where Jesus left\N—willingly—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.26,0:05:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to come down to be among us, to serve us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in the end, how far did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does verse 8 say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.77,0:05:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“More than that, when he came as a man,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“he humbled himself\Nand became obedient [to what?]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the point of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, death on a torture stake.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.61,0:05:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus was willing to go very, very far
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.53,0:05:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to help people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.00,0:05:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, you have all come to Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.46,0:05:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you come to Gilead?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.46,0:05:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the purpose of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.88,0:06:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nwas it to increase your Bible knowledge?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.09,0:06:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it to give you\Nsome grand knowledge of Bible history
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or to give you\Nsome comprehensive knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of Biblical Greek or Hebrew?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of your coming to Gilead
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.19,0:06:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was to help you so that you could strengthen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and stabilize the field and branch territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.32,0:06:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the purpose of Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But now,\Nwhat is the field and the branch territory?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.78,0:06:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s people\N—it’s people that need to be loved;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s people that need to be organized;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.75,0:06:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s people that need\Nto be trained and helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And at Gilead, you have learned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.42,0:06:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that Colossians 4:11
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.97,0:06:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,says to be “a source of great comfort” or,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.97,0:06:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as the footnote says,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.01,0:06:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to be “a strengthening aid” to other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.73,0:06:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, the question\Nthat sits before you now is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.94,0:07:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How far will you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.78,0:07:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How far will you go to be\Nfathers and mothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.20,0:07:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to be brothers and sisters\Nto all of these ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There has never been a need,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,such a great need,\Nfor this type of help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We have now in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.42,0:07:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,more of our brothers\Nfacing persecution than we have ever seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.13,0:07:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we expect that that is going to increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In some lands, we have lawlessness
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on a level previously unheard of,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.18,0:07:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,where kidnapping and rampant violence\Noccur on a daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of our brothers\Nare facing anxieties and pressures
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.69,0:07:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have never ever\Nhad to experience before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They need your help;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.40,0:07:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they need to be strengthened\Nand comforted by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.08,0:07:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sometimes\Nyou’re going to feel overwhelmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:08:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you’re going to wonder,\N‘What should I do?’
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.46,0:08:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you won’t know exactly what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.25,0:08:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes even your best efforts\Nof working very, very hard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,won’t work out the way\Nthat you want them to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.64,0:08:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember that the brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.93,0:08:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’re working with,\Nthe people that you’re trying to help,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are wonderful people,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.69,0:08:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will work with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.15,0:08:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will support you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But most of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.19,0:08:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,our wonderful and amazing God, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,will be there to support you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.99,0:08:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s an experience that I just heard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that really brought this\Nto my mind and strengthened it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from Abaco in the Bahamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you remember that just about a week ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we had this terrible Hurricane Dorian\Nthat struck this part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.34,0:08:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Disaster Relief Committee in the Bahamas
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.76,0:08:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,was working very hard to evacuate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.39,0:08:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers from Abaco Island to Nassau.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.97,0:08:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they had an airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:09:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They worked very hard to have\Nan airplane ready to go in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And although almost all communication\Nhad been cut off with Abaco Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.57,0:09:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they sent a message on all possible channels
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.74,0:09:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for the brothers in Abaco\Nto make their way to the airstrip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.16,0:09:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as they were loading\Nthe plane with all the necessary materials,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they were told that the government
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,would not grant permission\Nfor the plane to land that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.71,0:09:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the brothers tried everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They persisted, 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but the government authorities\Nwould not budge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.76,0:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how they felt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.80,0:09:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But an hour or so later,\Nmuch to their surprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.05,0:09:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they heard reports\Nthat 14 brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.35,0:09:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from Abaco would be landing soon in Nassau.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.23,0:09:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And they wondered,\N‘How could this be possible?’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.15,0:09:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they made preparations immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Nassau Assembly Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.82,0:09:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and 14 exhausted, hungry brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,arrived who had just been evacuated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a congregation meeting\Njust ending at the Assembly Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.00,0:10:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers all went out greeting them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.17,0:10:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and singing our new song “Unfailing Love.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.17,0:10:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine what the scene\Nmust have been there at Nassau?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.01,0:10:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, the question was,\NHow could this have happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the brothers explained:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.47,0:10:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“We heard the message to go to the airstrip,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.80,0:10:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“so we made our journey there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.14,0:10:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“A plane arrived,\Nand we thought it was the brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.94,0:10:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“but it was a company\Nwho had a plane circling the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.40,0:10:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“When they saw\Na group of people at the airstrip,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.73,0:10:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they landed and evacuated us.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.16,0:10:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourteen of the brothers got the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They followed the direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They assembled to be rescued,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Disaster Relief Committee said,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah made sure that his people\Nwere evacuated to safety.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.96,0:10:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.60,0:11:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So even when your best\Ndoesn’t seem to be good enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.35,0:11:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will make up for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.89,0:11:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best, and Jehovah will do the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.86,0:11:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have love for God
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have love\Nfor your brothers in your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,how far will you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.95,0:11:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You will go very, very far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.58,0:11:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re looking\Nforward now to our first talk
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.83,0:11:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from a member of the Governing Body,\Nour dear Brother Samuel Herd,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is going to give us\Na very fine warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,His talk is entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be Careful! ‘Knowledge Puffs Up.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.73,0:11:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.98,0:11:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m looking at you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.99,0:11:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have something that I can’t see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.91,0:12:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s in your head and in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.50,0:12:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.50,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve been cramming now for five months,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.75,0:12:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,stuffing things into that brain
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.38,0:12:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and allowing it through meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to trickle down into your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So you may feel that you have enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.14,0:12:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“I can’t get any more into the brain.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.15,0:12:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.31,0:12:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s still room for you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.03,0:12:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to put a little more knowledge\Ninto the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.53,0:12:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re going to do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.78,0:12:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may feel right now\Nthat you are ready to explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.49,0:12:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.87,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s something to think about:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Knowledge puffs up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.75,0:12:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but love builds up.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.34,0:13:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s a scripture\Nfound at 1 Corinthians 8:1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.35,0:13:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it doesn’t have to be this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.89,0:13:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,especially with divine knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.31,0:13:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowledge that you receive from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.35,0:13:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not designed to puff you up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.77,0:13:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make you feel better\Nthan your neighbors
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.03,0:13:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—your brothers and your sisters—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.03,0:13:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,who may not have the amount\Nof knowledge and education
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have\Nand what you have just now received.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that’s not the purpose\Nof the knowledge that you have acquired
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.87,0:13:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,here in Gilead School.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.96,0:13:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is something\Nwe have to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.46,0:13:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.88,0:13:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s open our Bibles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.88,0:13:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s open our Bibles to 2 Peter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.64,0:13:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at what is stated here at 2 Peter
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.56,0:13:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the first chapter, verses 5 and 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:14:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “For this very reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.07,0:14:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“put forth all earnest effort\Nto supply to your faith virtue,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.36,0:14:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“to your virtue knowledge,\Nto your knowledge self-control,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.83,0:14:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“to your self-control endurance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.71,0:14:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to your endurance godly devotion.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.13,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what you must apply\Nto your knowledge?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-control.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t allow our mouths to just run wild
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with the information that we’ve received
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.85,0:14:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—just spreading it everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.93,0:14:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t matter who may receive it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but you have to control
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.23,0:14:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,how much knowledge you permit
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.82,0:14:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to flow out of your mouth at a given time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.95,0:14:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-control is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.95,0:14:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means we should not boast\Nover our accomplishments.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.66,0:14:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All glory must go to Jehovah God
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and not to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.13,0:15:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s easy for others
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel that we are putting them\Ndown a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the vast knowledge that we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.97,0:15:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to be careful\Nand control it and not boast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminded me of a story,\Na fable, I heard years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.27,0:15:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,about a little flea by the name of Herman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Herman the Flea got on the back\Nof a giant elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And he rode on that elephant\Nacross the rickety bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.87,0:15:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bridge just shook as if it was\Ngoing to explode and fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.87,0:15:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But they made it to the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.13,0:15:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they made it to the other side\Nand the flea left the elephant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and found his friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.71,0:15:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he bragged about what he was able to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.72,0:15:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the elephant,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.72,0:15:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in making that bridge shake\Nas they crossed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.14,0:16:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how much do you feel\Nthat that flea contributed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.10,0:16:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to the shaking of that bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.52,0:16:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what we’re going to do, though—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.53,0:16:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to leave the fable,\Nand we’re going to go to the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.61,0:16:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go to the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.61,0:16:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to trade that flea\Nin for a grasshopper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here it is—Isaiah 40:22.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at it:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.33,0:16:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is One who dwells\Nabove the circle of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“and its inhabitants are like grasshoppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.68,0:16:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“He is stretching out the heavens\Nlike a fine gauze,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and he spreads them out\Nlike a tent to dwell in.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what we can do is we\Ncan apply this to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.69,0:16:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course,\Nin this scripture’s context,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.57,0:16:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is really not talking\Nabout his people as grasshoppers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.32,0:16:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but of people with worldly knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that they’ve acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:16:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They are like grasshoppers\Nas far as Jehovah is concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.75,0:17:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the whole context\Nof what he’s talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.75,0:17:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But we’re going to apply it to ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are so small\Nin the eyes of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.55,0:17:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can be just like a grasshopper
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,on the back of a giant elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.51,0:17:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And our accomplishments that we make
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.52,0:17:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are not of our own abilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s because of the help that we have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from heaven—Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we find that the apostle Paul
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.91,0:17:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,set a fine example of not being a braggart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.66,0:17:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he have?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.87,0:17:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he had so much knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, when known\Nas the man Saul of Tarsus,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.13,0:17:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he was highly educated and was a Pharisee,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.50,0:17:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was viewed\Nas an impeccable Jewish pedigree
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that this man had.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.22,0:17:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he wrote letters,\Nhe didn’t glorify himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.60,0:18:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance,\Ntake a look at 1 Corinthians chapter 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.27,0:18:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and read along with me verses 1 through 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.27,0:18:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’ll find that he did not\Nallow knowledge to puff him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how it reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“So when I came to you, brothers,\NI did not come with extravagant speech
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“or wisdom declaring\Nthe sacred secret of God to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I decided not to know anything\Namong you except Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.17,0:18:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“and him executed on the stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I came to you in weakness\Nand in fear and with much trembling;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“and my speech and what I preached were
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“not with persuasive words of wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.68,0:18:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“but with a demonstration\Nof spirit and power,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.10,0:18:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that your faith might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“not in men’s wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but in God’s power.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.40,0:18:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s the example.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s try our best to follow that example
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.65,0:18:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and not be like men and women of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.99,0:19:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who attend these great universities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.41,0:19:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And they come out,\Nand they’re able to get doctorate degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.96,0:19:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in science or this or that,\Nand they kind of show all that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.96,0:19:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But we’re not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.55,0:19:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But we could be if we’re not careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Bible shows
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.51,0:19:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what worldly wisdom can accomplish\Nand what it cannot accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, in Ecclesiastes 1:16-18,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.94,0:19:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the account starts off this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.69,0:19:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Then I said in my heart: ‘Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.07,0:19:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I have acquired great wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘more than anyone\Nwho was before me in Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.87,0:19:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and my heart gained a great deal\Nof wisdom and knowledge.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.74,0:19:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes on:\N“I applied my heart to knowing wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.33,0:19:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to knowing madness and to knowing folly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.67,0:19:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“and this too is a chasing after the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.84,0:19:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“For an abundance of wisdom\Nbrings an abundance of frustration,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.51,0:20:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so that whoever increases\Nknowledge increases pain.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you’ve got a little whiff of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Know-it-all,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.19,0:20:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then blow it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Move away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t want to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s never try to be a know-it-all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.87,0:20:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus doesn’t know everything\Nthat he has been learning
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.04,0:20:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah for aeons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.66,0:20:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how long is an aeon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,An aeon is a really, really, superlong,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.29,0:20:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible-to-measure length of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s an aeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.97,0:20:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Jehovah knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.59,0:20:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.60,0:20:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing beyond his understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.35,0:20:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.77,0:20:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Bible tells us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.19,0:20:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That same chapter where he mentions\Na grasshopper
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.19,0:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—Isaiah chapter 40—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.23,0:20:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but this time verses 13 and 14 say:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:21:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who has taken the measurements\Nof the spirit of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.45,0:21:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“and who can instruct him as [an] adviser?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.16,0:21:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“With whom did he consult\Nto gain understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.37,0:21:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“or who teaches him in the path of justice,\Nor teaches him knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or shows him the way of true understanding?”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.84,0:21:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We can know what we need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.47,0:21:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time we need to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.14,0:21:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s a mouthful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.14,0:21:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should we say, “a headful”?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.35,0:21:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, all of you graduates of Gilead School,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,please share with others\Nwhat you’ve learned here at Gilead School.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.61,0:21:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t walk away from this talk thinking\Nyou should keep your mouths closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.66,0:21:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.08,0:21:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But control what you say and when you say it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.96,0:21:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and to whom you tell it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:22:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that you’ve learned\Nso much at this school,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.97,0:22:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but share it discreetly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.39,0:22:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind these words of King Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.76,0:22:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: “There is an appointed time\Nfor everything, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.77,0:22:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a time to be silent and a time to speak.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.15,0:22:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t point to yourselves; point heavenward.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.07,0:22:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Always glorify Jehovah; point to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.03,0:22:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Governing Body members\N—all of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.37,0:22:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to be very careful ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.79,0:22:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because we get credit for things\Nthat we are not responsible for.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.08,0:22:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers will come and hug you:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.08,0:22:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh, thank you, brother,\Nyou Governing Body member
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.00,0:22:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—you really, wow, whoo, how, wah!”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.26,0:22:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know we didn’t do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.27,0:22:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have done\Nwhat we did if you’d been in our seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.27,0:23:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Jehovah’s spirit that causes\Nthese things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.27,0:23:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s true that we’re tools that he uses,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but he’s the One.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.57,0:23:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we’re not saying that you can’t say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.78,0:23:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Thank you, brother,\Nfor what you’re doing, the work that you do.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.58,0:23:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we’re not saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.08,0:23:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.83,0:23:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful that you’re not glorifying men,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.79,0:23:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but glorify God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.29,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body gets credit\Nthat we don’t deserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It belongs to Jehovah and Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.93,0:23:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we haven’t been able to close the mouths
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.89,0:23:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of over eight million bleating sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.43,0:23:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But we will keep trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.23,0:23:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So in conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.78,0:23:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,be like the grasshopper\Nthat rode on the back of the elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.66,0:23:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close to Jehovah, and enjoy the ride;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.66,0:23:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but always give Him the credit
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.45,0:23:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for your accomplishments.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.76,0:24:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we thank you so much, Brother Herd,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.89,0:24:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for that excellent warning for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.93,0:24:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the one day\NI mention insects in my introduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.31,0:24:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Herd uses insects in his talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.98,0:24:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we do need to know about insects.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.48,0:24:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now we’re looking forward to hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.53,0:24:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from a helper to the Service Committee\Nof the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.24,0:24:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Christopher Mavor,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.24,0:24:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and Brother Mavor\Nis going to speak to us on the topic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.91,0:24:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Count Your Days.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.87,0:24:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it true that we often “count our days”\Nwhen we anticipate an exciting event?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.29,0:24:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And no doubt you Gilead students
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,were counting your days\Nin anticipation of this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.84,0:24:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, if you were,\Nyou know that today is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.51,0:24:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the 138th day\Nof your Gilead School experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.56,0:25:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But after today,\Nwill you continue to ‘count your days’?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.44,0:25:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.15,0:25:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To answer that question,\Nplease open your Bibles to the 90th Psalm,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.61,0:25:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s a prayer that Moses said to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.40,0:25:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And notice what Moses\Nasked him in verse 12:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.37,0:25:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Teach us how to count our days
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.37,0:25:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we may acquire a heart of wisdom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.08,0:25:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the answer to this question is,\NYes, we should continue to count our days.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.09,0:25:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does that mean—count your days?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.80,0:25:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And why will we need God’s help to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.05,0:25:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is this:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.06,0:25:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are dedicated servants\Nof Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.35,0:25:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Each and every day,\Nwe need to make sure that we are using it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.69,0:25:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in his service to bring him glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.78,0:25:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we’re imperfect,\Nso this is not always easy to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.66,0:25:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, if we look at verse 10\Nof the 90th Psalm,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.20,0:25:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice that Moses said\Nthat our days are few
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.70,0:26:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are filled\Nwith a lot of difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.04,0:26:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need God’s help\Nto fulfill our dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.46,0:26:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we need to count our days,\Nand Jehovah promises
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.46,0:26:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will be there to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.97,0:26:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice this promise at Isaiah 30:21.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.01,0:26:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says: “And your own ears\Nwill hear a word behind you saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.64,0:26:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘This is the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.56,0:26:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Walk in it,’ 
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.40,0:26:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in case you should go to the right\Nor in case you should go to the left.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.03,0:26:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reality is that we need Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.45,0:26:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us to live a dedicated life to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.41,0:26:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully,\Nwe don’t need to figure it out on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.70,0:26:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s there to guide and direct us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.70,0:26:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you note what he expects of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.00,0:26:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking back at that scripture,\Nhe says that when he tells you something,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.88,0:26:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“walk in it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.17,0:26:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s an emphatic statement, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.30,0:26:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t leave any doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.30,0:26:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to do it\Nand make it happen in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.10,0:27:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot be passive about our dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.27,0:27:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as Christians,\Nwe live a very busy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.69,0:27:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We have various events to go to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.69,0:27:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And especially\Nif you’re in full-time service,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.73,0:27:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,well, you are given an assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.77,0:27:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and oftentimes\Nthat assignment is spelled out for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.90,0:27:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and even the schedule in which\Nto accomplish that work is set for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.74,0:27:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t really need\Nto think too much about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.70,0:27:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we’re not careful,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.83,0:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we could just get carried along\Nwith the flow of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.00,0:27:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the flow of the work and not remember
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.00,0:27:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,why we are doing it\Nand who we are doing it for.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.09,0:27:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we could become like\Nthis fine young brother on a raft.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.26,0:27:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He is enjoying himself;\Nhe’s going with the flow of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.47,0:27:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But is he really mindful\Nof where he is going and why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.39,0:27:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s sitting down; he’s looking all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.48,0:27:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The oar is not in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.31,0:27:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s not actively steering his life;\Nhe’s passive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.86,0:27:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, being passive\Nin our dedication to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.49,0:28:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very dangerous situation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.28,0:28:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because as Ecclesiastes 9:11 tells us:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.29,0:28:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Time and unexpected events overtake us.’
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.00,0:28:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this fine brother\Nis about to get a rude awakening.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.71,0:28:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,An unexpected rock has popped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.09,0:28:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A sudden storm of difficulties\Nhas overtaken him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.55,0:28:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he was passive,\Nhe was caught off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.05,0:28:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He lost his balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.68,0:28:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he’s suffering spiritual shipwreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.85,0:28:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not count his days.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.39,0:28:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He forgot to listen to Jehovah God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.81,0:28:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and to pay attention\Nto his dedication in his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.48,0:28:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn’t listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.57,0:28:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus emphasized\Nthat it’s so important for us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.66,0:28:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not to be passive\Nabout our dedication to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.83,0:28:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At Luke 13:24, Jesus made it clear
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.00,0:28:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are to ‘exert ourselves vigorously,’
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.04,0:28:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not just at a work assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.88,0:28:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but in our life as a Christian
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.92,0:29:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—being personally involved in what\Nwe are doing in our Christian dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.93,0:29:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul also gave good counsel\Nto the young man Timothy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.14,0:29:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that we benefit from today.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.81,0:29:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Timothy 4:7,\Nyou’ll recall that Paul said:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.10,0:29:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Train yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.19,0:29:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with godly devotion as your aim.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.24,0:29:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we’re training ourselves,\Nthat means we’re not finished yet;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.57,0:29:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re still in the competition;\Nwe’re still in training.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.33,0:29:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Godly devotion\Nmust be something that we personally do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.66,0:29:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for ourselves and work at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.08,0:29:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It just doesn’t happen on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.71,0:29:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But thankfully, Jehovah helps us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.05,0:29:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s given us his Word, the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.05,0:29:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s given us his organization, which\Nhelps us apply Bible principles in our life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.39,0:29:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and gives us warnings\Non the things to look out for.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.81,0:29:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s up to us to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.89,0:29:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s as if Jehovah gives us the oar,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.40,0:29:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says, ‘Now pick it up,\Nand use it in your stream of time.’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.53,0:30:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do,\Nthen we’re like this young brother now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.61,0:30:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s taking a firm hold on the oar.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.82,0:30:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s using it even during\Npeaceful times in his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.29,0:30:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,making sure that his life is continuing on\Nin a faithful Christian course.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.29,0:30:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when he encounters\Ntemptations or trials,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.09,0:30:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,well, he’s got his oar in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.22,0:30:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is there to help him\Nand to guide and direct him,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.09,0:30:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to navigate through the difficult times.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.43,0:30:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes effort;\Nit can be distressing,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.56,0:30:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah has given us the means
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.94,0:30:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to navigate through these difficult times\Nand to continue on in pursuing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.82,0:30:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our dedicated Christian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.07,0:30:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus set the perfect example in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.28,0:30:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, Jesus relied\Nheavily on Jehovah’s direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.25,0:30:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not take it for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.71,0:30:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus knew that when he was sent\Nto the earth, he had an assignment;
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.42,0:31:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he was on a very strict time budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.88,0:31:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was humanly impossible, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.38,0:31:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for a man, even a perfect man,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.89,0:31:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to accomplish what Jesus did.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.89,0:31:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He relied on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.93,0:31:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not take a casual viewpoint of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.31,0:31:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but every day he looked to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.27,0:31:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to help him to apply the principles\Nthat he learned through His Word
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.28,0:31:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—the direction that he received\Nfrom Jehovah God
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.03,0:31:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in going through this difficult assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.07,0:31:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus knew at the end of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.12,0:31:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—after the things he preached\Nand the things he did—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.12,0:31:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that that was a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.79,0:31:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He said so at John 14:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.21,0:31:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “The Father who remains\Nin union with me is doing his works.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.47,0:31:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that Jehovah was backing him up,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.05,0:31:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jesus worked with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.85,0:31:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t take a casual view of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.77,0:31:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we can have\Nthe same kind of confidence in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.06,0:32:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He is there for us,\Neven when we are encountering something
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.73,0:32:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that we feel is humanly impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.07,0:32:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a good example of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.49,0:32:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a couple\Nwho graduated in the 24th class of Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.95,0:32:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Their names are Malcolm and Grace Allen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.62,0:32:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, their life story\Nis in the October 15, 2013, {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower, 
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.79,0:32:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s really worthwhile reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.79,0:32:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We will find that in their early life\Nthey both pioneered;
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.92,0:32:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they got married; they pioneered together;
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.09,0:32:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they were in the circuit work\Nfor a number of years;
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.18,0:32:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they were invited to Gilead;
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.18,0:32:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and after Gilead,\Nthey were assigned to Brooklyn Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.81,0:32:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And there Brother Allen served\Nin some very responsible positions,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.52,0:32:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and his wife was a housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.56,0:32:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They loved their Bethel service.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.36,0:32:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But 25 years into their Bethel career,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.82,0:32:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,their course in life took a sudden change\N—a detour.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.32,0:32:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Unexpectedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.49,0:32:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,both sets of parents\Nbecame very ill and needy,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.41,0:32:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and it became apparent that they\Nwould have to relinquish their Bethel service
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.21,0:33:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and full-time service\Nin order to care for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.63,0:33:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, mind you, at this point in their life,\Nthey’re both in their late 50’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.26,0:33:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They used their youth in service to God,\Nso Brother Allen did not really have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.26,0:33:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a secular career\Nor a skill on which to go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.97,0:33:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He needed to start in his late 50’s
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.35,0:33:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the breadwinner of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.73,0:33:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Allen now needed\Nto take care of both sets of parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.07,0:33:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a sharp change in events for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.40,0:33:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but they held firm to their oar
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.53,0:33:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah God had given them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.66,0:33:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They learned to rely on Jehovah God\Nand to lean on him
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.50,0:33:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,every inch of the way,\Nand they were successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.37,0:33:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Allen found a job\Nas an insurance salesman,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.75,0:33:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which provided for the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.21,0:33:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And they kept going,\Neven though it was stressful times.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.17,0:33:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They were successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.26,0:33:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, eventually,\Ntheir parents died, and they thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.85,0:33:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, maybe\Nwe can return to Bethel service.’
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.18,0:34:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately,\Nat this point in their life,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.02,0:34:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,their own health and age overtook them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.15,0:34:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they had to be content with being
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.73,0:34:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,good, local, congregation publishers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.94,0:34:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they view this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.95,0:34:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this a view of failure on their part?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.07,0:34:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they think, ‘I failed’ or ‘I’m bitter\Nbecause of things that happened’?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.29,0:34:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Brother Allen makes\Nthis very profound statement
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.12,0:34:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,about life in Jehovah’s service.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.88,0:34:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.05,0:34:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“Life is unpredictable at times, uncertain,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.05,0:34:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“and even hard to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.14,0:34:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“But Jehovah blesses those who lean on him,\Nnot on their own understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.14,0:34:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is what my wife and I have experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.60,0:34:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,over our long and rewarding life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.19,0:34:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They rejoiced in their life\Nas dedicated servants of God
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.86,0:34:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by taking advantage\Nof every opportunity to express
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.74,0:34:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,their dedication to him
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.82,0:35:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and pursuing and practicing\Ngodly devotion in their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.33,0:35:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And they saw Jehovah’s hand
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.33,0:35:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in their life in truly miraculous ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.17,0:35:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they will experience\Nanother miracle of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.21,0:35:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because both of them\Nare now sleeping in the grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.09,0:35:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know that Jehovah\Nhas already calculated the days
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.76,0:35:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,when he will resurrect Malcolm and Grace
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.51,0:35:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and bring them back to life\Nso that they can continue serving him
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.35,0:35:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in a dedicated way\Nfor an eternity of days to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.27,0:35:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is certainly\Na good lesson for all of us:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.61,0:35:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to count our days\Nand to be fully invested in our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.24,0:35:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as a dedicated Christian to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.49,0:35:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you Gilead students\Nand really all of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.41,0:35:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,let us continue to lean on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.79,0:35:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and to work vigorously\Nat doing what Jehovah directs us to do
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.17,0:35:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,during these difficult last days\N—living up to our dedication to God!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.51,0:35:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And by doing so, we can be assured
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.97,0:36:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that we too will be blessed by Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.05,0:36:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He will give us an eternity of days to enjoy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.81,0:36:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in his glorious new world soon to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.40,0:36:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we thank you very much, Brother Mavor,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.45,0:36:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for that very good reminder.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.99,0:36:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now we have the privilege to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.24,0:36:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,from one of our more recently\Nappointed helpers to the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.54,0:36:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—Brother Leonard Myers—\Na helper to the Writing Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.79,0:36:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to speak to us on the topic
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.00,0:36:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You Trusted in Me.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.09,0:36:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“You trusted in me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.43,0:36:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you may be saying:\N“Brother Myers, I don’t even know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.43,0:36:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I trust in you?”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.81,0:36:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true that we need\Nto have a relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.02,0:36:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with an individual to truly trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.02,0:36:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But the “me” in our talk title\Nisn’t referring to any human;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.69,0:36:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s referring to our\Ntrustworthy God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.36,0:37:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that phrase\N“you trusted in me” was stated
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.78,0:37:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,by Jehovah to the faithful man Ebed-melech.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.58,0:37:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why could Jehovah tell him that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.87,0:37:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can his example help you students?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.37,0:37:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, turn with me, please,\Nto Jeremiah chapter 38.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.67,0:37:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we review his example,\Nlook for ways
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.63,0:37:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that Ebed-melech trusted in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.22,0:37:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you know,\NEbed-melech was an Ethiopian eunuch
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.43,0:37:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,employed in the house of King Zedekiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.93,0:37:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was a friend of the prophet Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.35,0:37:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, Jerusalem\Nwas under siege by the Babylonians,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.15,0:37:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jeremiah had repeatedly declared\Nthat this city was doomed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.23,0:37:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He had encouraged the people\Nto save themselves by surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.82,0:37:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that enraged certain princes\Nwho were Zedekiah’s advisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.33,0:37:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They were determined\Nto defend the city at all costs,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.62,0:37:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jeremiah was an obstacle to that defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.83,0:37:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you look in verse 4\Nof Jeremiah chapter 38,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.50,0:38:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the princes went to Zedekiah,\Nand they accused Jeremiah of weakening
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.63,0:38:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the morale of the soldiers\Nand all the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.85,0:38:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Weak king that he was,\NZedekiah stated in verse 5:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.52,0:38:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look! He is in your hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.52,0:38:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for the king cannot do anything to stop you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.61,0:38:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we know what that resulted in.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.61,0:38:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Those princes had Jeremiah\Nlowered into a miry, muddy cistern.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.91,0:38:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,With the food supply\Nbeing virtually exhausted in Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.91,0:38:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no hope\Nof Jeremiah receiving food from anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.50,0:38:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,His death was just a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.38,0:38:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in stepped Ebed-melech.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.79,0:38:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He heard what those princes had done,\Nand trusting in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.22,0:38:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he approached the king,\Nnot privately and not secretly,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.09,0:38:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but in public at one of the city gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.93,0:38:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And notice what he stated in verse 9:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.77,0:38:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“O my lord the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.10,0:38:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“what these men have done\Nto Jeremiah the prophet is evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.69,0:39:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“They have thrown him into the cistern,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.07,0:39:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will die there because of the famine,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.65,0:39:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for there is no bread left in the city.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.53,0:39:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the result\Nof his bold action and trust in Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.20,0:39:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The king stated in verse 10:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.08,0:39:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take 30 men with you from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.92,0:39:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and pull Jeremiah the prophet\Nup out of the cistern before he dies.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.80,0:39:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, 30 men certainly\Nwould have served as a protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.47,0:39:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, Ebed-melech may still have feared\Nwhat those princes would do to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.01,0:39:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But his concern was outweighed\Nby his friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.18,0:39:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and respect for Jehovah’s prophet
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.27,0:39:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and by his trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.98,0:39:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we know, verses 11-13\Noutline his successful rescue mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.45,0:39:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But why could Ebed-melech be so courageous
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.53,0:39:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when he approached\Nthe king and rescued Jeremiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.33,0:39:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because he trusted in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.33,0:39:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of that trust,\Nnotice how Jehovah would reward him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.71,0:40:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In chapter 39, we’ll start reading\Nin the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}B {\r} portion of verse 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.42,0:40:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Jehovah’s words\Nthrough Jeremiah to Ebed-melech:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.76,0:40:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Here I am fulfilling my words\Non this city for calamity and not for good,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.85,0:40:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and in that day you will see it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.81,0:40:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I will rescue you\Nin that day,’ declares Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.02,0:40:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and you will not be handed over\Nto the men you fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.11,0:40:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For I will surely provide you with escape,\Nand you will not fall by the sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.03,0:40:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You will have your life as a spoil,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.49,0:40:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because you trusted in me.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.91,0:40:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ebed-melech didn’t need to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.91,0:40:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As he had viewed Jeremiah’s life as precious,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.87,0:40:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so Jehovah viewed his life as precious
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.92,0:40:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and would preserve him alive
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.92,0:40:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—all because, as verse 18 says,\N‘he trusted in Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.93,0:40:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, whether he was deported\Nto Babylon and died a natural death
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.10,0:40:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or was left back in the land of Judah,\Nthe Bible doesn’t say, 
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.48,0:40:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but his life would be spared,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.94,0:41:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and he could continue to worship\Nthe God in whom he trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.07,0:41:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point,\NEbed-melech vanishes from Bible history
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.15,0:41:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but not his name nor the example \Nthat he set for you and me
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.33,0:41:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.75,0:41:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this thought of trusting\Nin Jehovah isn’t new to you students.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.62,0:41:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting in Jehovah got you to Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.84,0:41:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In your assignments at Bethel or the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.30,0:41:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you proved your trust in God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.26,0:41:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust helped you\Nthrough your studies at Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.89,0:41:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the times\Nwhen you prayed for Jehovah’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.51,0:41:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with an assignment or a test 
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.81,0:41:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or, as one recent graduate said,\N“when your brain was full and you needed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.02,0:41:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a full week off to digest all the material”?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.48,0:41:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember those times?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.52,0:41:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that took trust\Nthat Jehovah would help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.94,0:41:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you look to the future,\Ntrusting in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.32,0:41:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you to be successful\Nin your assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.58,0:42:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice these comments from graduates\Nof the last class of Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.12,0:42:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,One brother wrote: \N“We have placed our lives in Jehovah’s hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.13,0:42:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“We pray to Jehovah\Nwith an intensity and trust
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.84,0:42:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that never existed before.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.43,0:42:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Another brother wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.72,0:42:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“At times I have felt like, ‘What do we do?’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.68,0:42:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then I’m reminded that we confidently leave\Nthe matter in Jehovah’s hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.14,0:42:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,trusting that he will handle it\Nor make clear to us the course to take.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.57,0:42:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally another brother wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.90,0:42:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“At times we have felt quite overwhelmed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.61,0:42:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the new language,\Nresponsibilities, culture, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.79,0:42:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“However, our trust in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.58,0:42:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“reminds us that this is his organization
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.17,0:42:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“—his work—\Nand they are his sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.58,0:42:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“If we do our part and work hard,\Nthere is no doubt that he’ll help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.42,0:42:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We never have to rely on ourselves.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.18,0:42:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Ebed-melech, trusting in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.06,0:43:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you\Nto be successful in your assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.35,0:43:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are two ways\Nthat you can add to your trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.36,0:43:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,(1) Trusting in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.82,0:43:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,involves trusting\Nin the power of holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.78,0:43:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Ntrusting in that spirit will help you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.03,0:43:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to deal with your brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.66,0:43:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your assignments\Nwill involve close contact with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.29,0:43:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Will there be challenges at times?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.92,0:43:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Very likely.\NWe’re all imperfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.92,0:43:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust that holy spirit can help you\Nto cultivate the love, 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.59,0:43:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,peace, patience, mildness, and self-control
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.76,0:43:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ll need\Nto deal with those situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.76,0:43:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(2) Trusting in Jehovah means
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.10,0:43:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,trusting those whom he trusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.73,0:43:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has arranged for\N“the faithful and discreet slave”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.28,0:43:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to care for earthly Kingdom interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.40,0:43:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in the appointment of the slave,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.78,0:44:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,trust in Jehovah’s arrangement,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.83,0:44:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,follow any direction that the slave provides.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.12,0:44:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are two ways\Nthat you can add to your trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.58,0:44:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage you to trust in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.04,0:44:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when you face\Nchallenging situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.96,0:44:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,During those times,\Nremember scriptures such as these:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.38,0:44:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 3:5:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.85,0:44:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Trust in Jehovah with all your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.06,0:44:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and do not rely on your own understanding”;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.23,0:44:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 56:3, 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.69,0:44:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I am afraid, I put my trust in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.44,0:44:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“In God\N—whose word I praise—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.03,0:44:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in God I put my trust”;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.41,0:44:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and Isaiah 26:3, 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.83,0:44:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will safeguard those\Nwho fully lean on you;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.92,0:44:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will give them continuous peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.33,0:44:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“because it is in you that they trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.25,0:44:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Jehovah forever.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.42,0:45:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Scriptures like those\Ncan really help you during challenging times.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.43,0:45:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust got you here to Gilead,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.68,0:45:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,trust helped you through your studies,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.89,0:45:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and trust in Jehovah\Nwill help you in your assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.56,0:45:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Ebed-melech,\Ncontinue to trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.19,0:45:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, one day I hope\Nto get to know all of you students.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.49,0:45:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can truly say\Nthat we trust one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.95,0:45:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, continue to trust in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.50,0:45:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he can say\Nof you dear Gilead students:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.62,0:45:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“You trusted in me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.18,0:45:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we thank you\Nfor that excellent advice, Brother Myers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.73,0:45:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we’re looking forward to hearing\Nfrom one of the Gilead instructors,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.48,0:45:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m sure all the students are going\Nto be interested to hear what he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.19,0:46:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother James Cauthon\Nis going to speak to us on the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.28,0:46:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Shaken but Not Forsaken.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.70,0:46:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.83,0:46:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, you become a graduate\Nof the 147th class of Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.71,0:46:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a day to be celebrated;\Nit’s a day to be enjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.55,0:46:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And you deserve it; you worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.38,0:46:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And even when you thought\Nyou had reached your limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.64,0:46:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn’t give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.68,0:46:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You kept coming in;\Nyou kept trusting in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.60,0:46:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As your instructors, we’re very pleased
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.23,0:46:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to see your happy, smiling faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.65,0:46:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we could, we’d wish that for you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.94,0:46:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,every day for the rest of your lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.16,0:46:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as much as we try,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.08,0:46:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we can’t control what happens\Nto us in life, isn’t that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.41,0:46:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,A change comes for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.04,0:46:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sooner or later, it’s inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.09,0:47:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Some changes are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.59,0:47:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Other changes,\Nhowever, can rock our world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.01,0:47:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave us shaken to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.60,0:47:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that happens,\Nwe may suddenly find
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.43,0:47:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’re no longer\Nthe person we thought we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.44,0:47:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It can seem as if our very identity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.48,0:47:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,has been ripped away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.78,0:47:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider Moses.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.94,0:47:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses grew up in one of the most\Nluxuriant places on earth at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.32,0:47:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, the Egyptian royal court.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.49,0:47:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Members of the royal household\Nresided in opulent mansions
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.71,0:47:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that were dotted along the Nile.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.08,0:47:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These homes\Nwere decorated in precious stones,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.21,0:47:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,incorporated with pools and gardens.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.05,0:47:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They housed a large staff\Nthat prepared lavish meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.64,0:47:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses likely had a knowledge\Nand understanding of some
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.97,0:47:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the most amazing structures\Nthe world has ever seen, and why?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.98,0:47:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Likely, it’s because\Nhe was schooled from a young age
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.61,0:48:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in subjects such as writing,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.69,0:48:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,math, science, and architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.11,0:48:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.16,0:48:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses may have witnessed\NEgypt’s rise to become a mighty empire
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.95,0:48:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and a powerful military force.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.87,0:48:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses enjoyed a privileged\Nand extravagant upbringing,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.79,0:48:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and no doubt he became\Na man of confidence and influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.63,0:48:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Acts 7:22 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.88,0:48:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Moses was instructed\Nin all the wisdom of the Egyptians.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.85,0:48:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he was powerful\Nin his words and deeds.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.64,0:48:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he killed an Egyptian\Non behalf of his fellow Hebrew brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.65,0:48:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he saw himself as a deliverer.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.78,0:48:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He was confident,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.86,0:48:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,he was ready, but he was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.70,0:48:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We know what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.32,0:48:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He fled to Midian.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.99,0:48:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He was no longer the favorite prince\Nand no longer in charge of anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.58,0:48:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,except some sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.12,0:49:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The confidence he knew back in Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.75,0:49:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,had been replaced\Nwith confusion, loss, and fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.42,0:49:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses must have been shaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.01,0:49:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So often, disappointments in life\Nbring on feelings of sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.97,0:49:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,self-doubt, and worthlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.73,0:49:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And those things, in effect,\Nstrip us of our cherished identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.73,0:49:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re especially vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.82,0:49:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,if we define ourselves\Nby our natural skills and qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.78,0:49:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or by what others think of us
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.20,0:49:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or even by our assignment or position.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.91,0:49:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, when we do that, we’re saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.75,0:49:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am what I do”\Nor “I am what others think of me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.25,0:49:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These are deceptive filters
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.80,0:49:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that cause us to lose sight\Nof who we really are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.59,0:49:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and, then, when change comes, \Nwe’re shaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.97,0:49:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But are we forsaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.47,0:50:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider Moses again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.39,0:50:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses was the chosen one to—
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.94,0:50:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Moses the chosen one\Nto deliver the Hebrews?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.23,0:50:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.57,0:50:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it Jehovah’s time?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.82,0:50:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is no,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.82,0:50:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and neither was he fully qualified\Nfor the appointment
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.03,0:50:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or the assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.08,0:50:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he needed divine training,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.79,0:50:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was something\Nthat he could not get in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.59,0:50:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that he had worldly education;\Nhe had confidence; he had poise,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.59,0:50:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but he needed the qualities\Nof patience, meekness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.64,0:50:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,humility, and self-control\Nto be developed to a greater degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.35,0:50:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah saw that,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.35,0:50:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and he knew just how to accomplish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.90,0:50:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be the lowly occupation\Nof being a shepherd in Midian.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.94,0:50:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after 40 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.61,0:50:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses sees the flaming thorn bush,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.95,0:51:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and to his surprise and shock,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.95,0:51:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah commissions him 40 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.96,0:51:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think about how Moses\Nmust have felt at that moment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.63,0:51:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—the realization that he wasn’t worthless
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.55,0:51:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Jehovah still valued him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.38,0:51:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,His daily pain of heart\Nover the suffering of his fellow Hebrews
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.39,0:51:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was now being replaced\Nwith a keen anticipation
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.39,0:51:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for what Jehovah was going to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.77,0:51:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and no doubt in a marvelous way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.07,0:51:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,\NMoses was never really forsaken by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.91,0:51:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.74,0:51:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, Jehovah had been with him\Nevery step of the way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.16,0:51:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,during those 40 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.33,0:51:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,molding him and preparing him\Nfor an incredible future assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.33,0:51:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that he could never have possibly imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.51,0:51:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will do the same for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.13,0:51:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, he takes a long-range view.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.93,0:52:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees your potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.93,0:52:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows how to accomplish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.60,0:52:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember that Jehovah\Nwill do it at the right time
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.60,0:52:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and at his time
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.94,0:52:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that his view must be our view.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.11,0:52:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So when a change comes,\Nwhatever it may be,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.49,0:52:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s just the scene;
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.66,0:52:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not the entire movie;
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.74,0:52:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s a chapter; it’s not the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.50,0:52:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not know\Nwhat’s coming next, but don’t worry,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.92,0:52:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.63,0:52:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Decades later, after leading\NJehovah’s people out of Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.63,0:52:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and navigating through the wilderness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.01,0:52:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it was now time for Joshua to step up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.31,0:52:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At Deuteronomy 31:8
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.06,0:52:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses said to Joshua:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.44,0:52:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah . . . will neither desert you\Nnor abandon you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.02,0:52:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Those must have been\Nvery encouraging words.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.74,0:53:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Moses never forgot the lesson\Nhe learned all those years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.28,0:53:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He had been shaken, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.83,0:53:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but he was not forsaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.50,0:53:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And perhaps that was his motivation\Nfor writing another passage in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.42,0:53:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See if you remember this:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.88,0:53:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“Anyone dwelling\Nin the secret place of the Most High
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.55,0:53:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“will lodge under the shadow of the Almighty.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.76,0:53:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will say to Jehovah:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.97,0:53:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You are my refuge and my stronghold,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.98,0:53:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,my God in whom I trust.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.60,0:53:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that sound familiar?—Psalm 91.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.15,0:53:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses had become absolutely convinced 
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.32,0:53:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was always with him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.95,0:53:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through the good times\Nand through the hard times.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.12,0:53:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So like Moses,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.33,0:53:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll experience joys
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.21,0:53:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and some disappointments
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.29,0:53:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and, sooner or later, change
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.34,0:53:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—perhaps a change\Naway from a cherished assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.59,0:54:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It may feel devastating.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.13,0:54:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either roll with it\Nor you can be rolled over by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.43,0:54:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How will you roll with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.43,0:54:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can roll with it if you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.60,0:54:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’re not your career;
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.73,0:54:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re not your assignment;\Nyou’re not your privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.86,0:54:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You are, however, loved by God,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.15,0:54:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a spiritual heritage,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.37,0:54:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have a wonderful, bright future.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.08,0:54:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you remember that,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.25,0:54:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you can gracefully\Naccept the changes that come.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.46,0:54:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s something else you can do:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.67,0:54:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use your experience to help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.21,0:54:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, your willingness \Nto help others even when you’re shaken
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.80,0:54:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by a personal experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.30,0:54:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will reveal your loyalty and your maturity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.60,0:54:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do little things\Nas if they were great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.06,0:54:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Small tasks reveal a big heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.98,0:55:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all a part of our training\Nnow and for life in the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.44,0:55:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember this too:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.65,0:55:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A change of circumstances\Nis rarely as important
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.16,0:55:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as a change of attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.54,0:55:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s not your position,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.04,0:55:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will be your disposition
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.88,0:55:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that will bring Jehovah’s blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.30,0:55:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So in conclusion: Yes, change will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.26,0:55:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The world changes;
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.26,0:55:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances change; we change.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.93,0:55:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Jehovah does not change,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.19,0:55:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,his Word does not change,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.35,0:55:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and his love for you will never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.69,0:55:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So while you may be shaken at times,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.94,0:55:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,rest assured,\Nyou will never ever be forsaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.55,0:56:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don’t know about you,\Nbut I marked down,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.22,0:56:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“It’s not your position;\Nit’s your disposition.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.64,0:56:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be using that one in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.64,0:56:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very, very much, Brother Cauthon,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.68,0:56:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for those excellent thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.73,0:56:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now we have the privilege to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.73,0:56:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from another of the Gilead instructors,\NBrother Mark Noumair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.90,0:56:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to speak to us on the topic
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.19,0:56:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember the Vision.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.78,0:56:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the rarest privileges
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.79,0:56:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a human has ever had
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.70,0:56:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is to see a vision of Jehovah’s throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.08,0:56:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s good for us now
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.46,0:56:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to look on with a man
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.92,0:56:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who had this privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.13,0:56:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and how the vision changed his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.30,0:56:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What were the circumstances\Naround this event?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.52,0:56:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And more importantly for you,\Nhow does it affect you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.90,0:57:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And what lessons\Ndo we want you to take to heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.65,0:57:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So please open your Bibles
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.36,0:57:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or listen closely to these words
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.49,0:57:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded at Isaiah 6:1.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.66,0:57:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 6:1:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.21,0:57:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the year that King Uzziah died,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.58,0:57:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“I saw Jehovah sitting
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.38,0:57:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“on a lofty and elevated throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.38,0:57:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and the skirts of his robe\Nfilled the temple.”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.55,0:57:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The skirts of Jehovah’s magnificent garment
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.68,0:57:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,filling the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.69,0:57:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—this is what Isaiah saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.94,0:57:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it show?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.94,0:57:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows that Jehovah\Nwas figuratively present in the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.32,0:57:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he was keenly aware of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.95,0:57:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that was going on there,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.95,0:57:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,including what had happened with King Uzziah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.12,0:58:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, recall that Uzziah
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.08,0:58:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was not content with his role as king.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.63,0:58:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.63,0:58:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He forced his way\Ninto the holy compartment of the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.80,0:58:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.84,0:58:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To burn incense like a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.97,0:58:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, he was struck with leprosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.68,0:58:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is of interest
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.81,0:58:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah inspired Isaiah to write,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.61,0:58:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the year
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.61,0:58:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jotham (Uzziah’s son) became king,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.61,0:58:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather,\N“in the year that King Uzziah died.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.49,0:58:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,By directing Isaiah to pen those words
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.16,0:58:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the year that Uzziah died,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.21,0:58:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it could be said\Nthat Jehovah was setting the stage
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.84,0:58:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for teaching Isaiah what qualities he loves
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.88,0:58:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and what qualities he hates.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.26,0:58:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, this vision is going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.26,0:59:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,life-changing for Isaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.68,0:59:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want it to be\Nlife-changing for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.06,0:59:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happens next?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.06,0:59:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, verse 2 shows\Nthat Jehovah reveals something
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.65,0:59:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps no other human has seen in vision
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.45,0:59:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—seraphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.45,0:59:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah is the only Bible writer\Nthat mentions them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.37,0:59:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the privileges these seraphs enjoy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.25,0:59:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—their high rank and serving close\Nto the Universal Sovereign—
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.26,0:59:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,move them to humbly cover their faces
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.18,0:59:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with their wings
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.22,0:59:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and sing Jehovah’s praises with such power
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.81,0:59:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that the temple foundation shakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.15,0:59:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What lesson in contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.77,0:59:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,could Jehovah have been impressing on Isaiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.28,0:59:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, consider this:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.86,1:00:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Uzziah became king at only 16 years old
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.87,1:00:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and showed\Ntremendous potential at the outset.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.91,1:00:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When Isaiah became a prophet,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.83,1:00:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he too was a young man,\Nmost likely in his twenties.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.75,1:00:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He was married to a supportive wife;\Nshe’s called a prophetess.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.97,1:00:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So by showing Isaiah\Nthe example of these humble seraphs
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.97,1:00:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same year Uzziah died,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.85,1:00:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it was as if Jehovah was saying:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.69,1:00:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You know, Isaiah, you’re a fine young man.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.48,1:00:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You have a bright future.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.49,1:00:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You have a good wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.49,1:00:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But don’t become presumptuous like Uzziah.’
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.45,1:00:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful contrast\Nfor Isaiah to meditate on!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.91,1:00:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt this affected him deeply.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.37,1:00:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is your first lesson:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.54,1:00:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Isaiah, you have a bright future.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.01,1:01:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t miss the purpose\Nof why you’ve been called to Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.97,1:01:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your assignment is to honor Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.14,1:01:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve been trained\Nto support his organization.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.73,1:01:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We are investing in you for the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.40,1:01:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So remember the vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.23,1:01:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitate the seraphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.53,1:01:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Cover your face,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.99,1:01:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and don’t spoil your humility
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.95,1:01:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,by drawing undue attention to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.58,1:01:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, even the most subtle boasting
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.71,1:01:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,invites others to take\Na peek at you and look in.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.55,1:01:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who are you?\NWhat are you doing?’
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.59,1:01:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that detracts from Jehovah’s glory.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.01,1:01:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So when tempted to blow your own horn,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.85,1:01:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,remember the mighty song of the seraphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.10,1:01:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sing Jehovah’s praises, not your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.39,1:01:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Any privilege you receive
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.81,1:01:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,should make you\Nmore humble like the seraphs,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.78,1:01:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,not puff you up like Uzziah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.57,1:02:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And by remaining humble,\NJehovah can use you to a greater extent.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.99,1:02:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.20,1:02:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he can trust you\Nto give him the glory.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.41,1:02:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Seraphs\N—they don’t aspire to be kings;
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.00,1:02:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they don’t aspire to be priests.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.00,1:02:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But they’re content\Nwith their role as workers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.34,1:02:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So be like the seraphs by doing your part
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.76,1:02:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to advance pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.85,1:02:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What else could Isaiah learn from this song?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.47,1:02:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, chapter 6, verse 3b says:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.23,1:02:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“The whole earth is filled with his glory.”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.57,1:02:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s an interesting statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.61,1:02:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why may Jehovah have included\Nthose words as part of the vision?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.32,1:02:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, consider this:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.78,1:02:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah was faced\Nwith extreme apathy in his assignment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.46,1:02:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The land of Judah was full of false worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.83,1:02:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The rebellious ten-tribe kingdom of Samaria\Nhad rejected Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.17,1:03:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To Isaiah, it could have felt\Nlike no one was glorifying Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.51,1:03:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Where’s the glory for Jehovah?’
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.80,1:03:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If he focused on those trials,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.60,1:03:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it could have been so easy for him\Nto get discouraged, to give up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.97,1:03:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What’s the use?\NWhy should I put up with this?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.18,1:03:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No one is listening.’
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.39,1:03:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what would help him not to give up?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.40,1:03:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He would need to go back to the vision
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.94,1:03:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and imagine a future time
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.20,1:03:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of the whole earth\Nbeing filled with Jehovah’s glory.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.66,1:03:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And with eyes of faith,\NIsaiah would focus on what Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.70,1:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was yet to accomplish as part of His purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.00,1:03:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah strengthened Isaiah\Nwith prophecies about the future
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.92,1:03:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when the whole earth\Nwould be filled with His glory
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.88,1:03:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—prophecies about the Messiah\Nand the restoration of true worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.68,1:03:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah himself even witnessed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.05,1:03:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the prophecy\Nbeing fulfilled in his own lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.02,1:03:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—the fall of the ten-tribe kingdom\Nto the Assyrians.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.44,1:04:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then more than 40 years later\Nafter his hard work,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.19,1:04:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine, he was honored to record
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.36,1:04:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the most spectacular demonstrations
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.82,1:04:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s executional power in all Scripture
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.58,1:04:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,—the destruction\Nof 185,000 soldiers in one night.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.21,1:04:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,An outstanding reminder:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.25,1:04:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Isaiah, my glory\Nis indeed filling the whole earth.’
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.00,1:04:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if Jehovah was saying:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.13,1:04:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Isaiah, listen;
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.30,1:04:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I know you see badness among people,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.76,1:04:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘but keep your focus.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.76,1:04:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Focus on the good things\Nthat I’m accomplishing right now
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.35,1:04:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and will accomplish in the future.’
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.27,1:04:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is lesson number two for you:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.48,1:04:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you find yourself\Nbecoming consumed with trials
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.53,1:04:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,—the imperfections of others
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.53,1:04:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(maybe some you work with two,\Nthree, four, five here and there),
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.91,1:04:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the frustrations of the work,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.95,1:04:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,being passed over again for a privilege,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.54,1:04:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and you start thinking:\N‘What’s the use of working hard?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.71,1:05:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why am I trying so hard to apply\Nthe good training I’ve received at Gilead?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.55,1:05:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No one here cares’
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.59,1:05:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—take a deep breath.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.59,1:05:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Back away;
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.59,1:05:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,return to the vision;
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.64,1:05:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,shift the focus off yourself\Nand onto the big picture,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.64,1:05:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the whole earth\Nbeing filled with Jehovah’s glory.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.61,1:05:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your focus\Non the 8.5 million people earth wide
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.53,1:05:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who are glorifying Jehovah God\Nin his great spiritual temple.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.16,1:05:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is playing\Na small but valuable role
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.99,1:05:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in accomplishing Jehovah’s purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.45,1:05:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do that,\Nit will help you to cherish
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.33,1:05:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,your place in God’s global arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.92,1:05:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Next comes the invitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.92,1:05:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The invitation\N—here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.80,1:05:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that invitation in verse 8
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.85,1:06:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is so real, so vivid,\Nto Isaiah that he’s moved to declare:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.35,1:06:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here I am! [Here I am!] Send me!”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.15,1:06:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No hesitation\N—he didn’t ask what he would gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.73,1:06:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t ask what other assignments\Nhis contemporary prophets got.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.24,1:06:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What about that one?\NWhat about this one?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.24,1:06:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s Micah going to do?\NHosea and what—?’
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.24,1:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.66,1:06:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He just said:\N“Here I am! Send me!”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.66,1:06:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that amazing?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.71,1:06:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact is he didn’t know\Neverything he was signing up for.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.88,1:06:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Those details would come later,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.88,1:06:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and they did
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.30,1:06:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—about 17 years later.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.55,1:06:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Isaiah is told to take\Nhis small son Shear-jashub
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.56,1:06:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and go meet King Ahaz\N—wicked King Ahaz—
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.23,1:06:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and offer him help.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.23,1:06:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, can you imagine?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.23,1:06:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah\N—what was he thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.53,1:06:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Now, wait a minute,\Nwait a minute, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.82,1:06:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Ahaz murders his own children,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.57,1:06:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and now you want me\Nto take my son along?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.99,1:07:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I said:\N“Here I am! Send me—not us.”’
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.37,1:07:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about his wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.79,1:07:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What about his wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.79,1:07:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Isaiah, you’re not taking my little boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.21,1:07:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shear-jashub, get back here.’
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.22,1:07:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you don’t know,\Nbut it just helps you to think about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.64,1:07:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So both Isaiah and his wife
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.81,1:07:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,would need to return\Nto the vision for reassurance
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.69,1:07:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah’s skirts, his attention,\Nwas indeed filling Judah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.61,1:07:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He was aware of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.61,1:07:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They would need to trust in Jehovah\N—follow his direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.74,1:07:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah, in effect, said:\N‘I’ll go; I’ll go.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.70,1:07:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be faithful even if the king is not.’
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.24,1:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah did not let\Nthe tests of others make him fail his.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.75,1:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesson number three:
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.92,1:07:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Assignments to support the Kingdom work
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.67,1:07:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are not always easy,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.22,1:07:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wives feel it too.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.93,1:08:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When your husband receives\Nan assignment perhaps no one else wants,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.77,1:08:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you play a crucial role.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.27,1:08:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How will you respond\Nwhen he tells you of the assignment?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.48,1:08:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why did they pick you?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.94,1:08:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Can’t you tell them to find someone else?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.94,1:08:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it last time.’
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.99,1:08:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Or will you be proud of your husband
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.66,1:08:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—proud of him for being Isaiah-like,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.74,1:08:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,accepting the assignments faithfully,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.95,1:08:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,even volunteering for them?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.04,1:08:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You wives,\Nyour support is priceless in God’s eyes,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.04,1:08:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can make all the difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.30,1:08:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you think\NIsaiah remembered the vision?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.72,1:08:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt he recalled\Nnot only the images but the sounds 
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.22,1:08:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s skirts stretching,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.43,1:08:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,filling the temple;
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.43,1:08:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the seraphs’ powerful wings\Nbeating through the air;
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.35,1:08:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the melodious words echoing in song.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.02,1:08:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They would no doubt be\Npermanently etched in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.94,1:08:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only imagine\Nthat Isaiah and his wife
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.45,1:09:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,replayed that vision\Nover and over again in their minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.16,1:09:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And how it must have helped\Nthem to hold on to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.29,1:09:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and never let go for those 40 plus years.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.67,1:09:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the vision can do the same for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.46,1:09:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the point.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.55,1:09:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This inspired vision, this holy scripture,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.05,1:09:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,can help you\Nto stick to Jehovah and never let go,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.76,1:09:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when times are hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.10,1:09:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are struggling\Nto keep afloat spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.56,1:09:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a challenge\Nyou have to overcome,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.60,1:09:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you might even feel at times\Nlike you’re swimming in mud,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.60,1:09:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t give up.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.61,1:09:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Make the vision come alive in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.15,1:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,See the images; hear the sounds;
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.19,1:09:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,feel the awe Isaiah must have felt.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.61,1:09:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then\N—and then apply the lessons in your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.41,1:09:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Apply these wonderful Scriptural lessons\Nin your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.91,1:09:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitate the seraphs:\NCover your face; stay humble.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.13,1:09:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,See God’s glory filling the whole earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.75,1:09:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the big picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.76,1:10:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep ablaze the “Here I am! Send me!” fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.59,1:10:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, remember the vision
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.89,1:10:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and let it motivate you\Nto keep your cherished place
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.89,1:10:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in God’s great spiritual temple now
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.77,1:10:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and in Jehovah’s heart for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.83,1:10:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we thank you so much, Brother Noumair,\Nfor those excellent thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.16,1:10:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It truly was\Na spiritually enriching Gilead program.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.71,1:10:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the coming weeks,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.92,1:10:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Parts 2 and 3 of the graduation
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.76,1:10:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will be released on JW Broadcasting,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.64,1:10:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so keep on the lookout.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.64,1:10:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll conclude this month’s program\Nby traveling to the island of Réunion,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.39,1:10:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,located in the Indian Ocean
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.90,1:10:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,between Madagascar
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.90,1:10:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mauritius.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.90,1:11:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s decorated\Nwith beautiful volcanic sand beaches,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.86,1:11:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,waterfalls,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.86,1:11:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,deep valleys, rugged peaks,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.45,1:11:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of the most\Nactive volcanoes on earth, 
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.79,1:11:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Piton de la Fournaise.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.04,1:11:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The first Kingdom publisher\Narrived to Réunion in 1955.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.38,1:11:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now more than 3,000
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.76,1:11:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of our brothers and sisters\Nare serving there;
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.14,1:11:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,over 400 of them are regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.43,1:11:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,While French\Nis the official language of the island,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.43,1:11:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there are 3 congregations in Malagasy
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.56,1:11:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and 13 in the common tongue\Nof Creole of Réunion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.57,1:11:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the brothers’ evangelizing spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.40,1:11:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,over 6,500 people on Réunion\Nattended the Memorial
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.66,1:11:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2018.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.41,1:11:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Grand Bois Congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.91,1:11:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They have more than 130 publishers,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.04,1:12:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with 13 regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.63,1:12:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And as of May 2019,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.09,1:12:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they were conducting 61 Bible studies.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.97,1:12:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is\Nthe Salazie Creole Congregation,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.56,1:12:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with just 21 publishers.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.89,1:12:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But they conduct 13 Bible studies!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.31,1:12:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,These warm and hospitable\Nbrothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.65,1:12:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in both Grand Bois and Salazie Creole
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.19,1:12:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,are working hard\Nto proclaim the Kingdom message.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.49,1:12:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We love our brothers in Réunion\Nand send them our greetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.12,1:12:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we love all of you faithful ones
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.41,1:12:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,who are viewing this program.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.08,1:12:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.75,1:12:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting!
